 </m:math>
m has not changed and is circular, calculate the approximate total distance Earth has traveled since its birth (in a frame of reference stationary with respect to the Sun).</para></problem>
        <solution id="fs-id1362022"><para id="fs-id3401076"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo stretchy="false">×</m:mo><m:msup><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mtext>21</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>m</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math></para></solution></exercise>
        <exercise id="fs-id2688068" type="problems-exercises">
          <problem id="fs-id1909383">
            <para id="fs-id3354583">The propeller of a World War II fighter plane is 2.30 m in diameter. </para>
