                   <exercise id="fs-id1993714" type="problems-exercises">
                     <problem id="fs-id1548317"><para id="fs-id3059556">Verify that the linear speed of an ultracentrifuge is about 0.50 km/s, and Earth in its orbit is about 30 km/s by calculating:</para>
                  <para id="fs-id3138086">(a) The linear speed of a point on an ultracentrifuge 0.100 m from its center, rotating at 50,000 rev/min.</para>
                  <para id="fs-id1595818">(b) The linear speed of Earth in its orbit about the Sun (use data from the text on the radius of Earth’s orbit and approximate it as being circular).</para>
                     </problem>
